The paper proposes a new approach to make ResNet architectures invertible, which can be used for classification, density estimation, and generation. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and information theory (cs.IT).
